# D-70 disk-cache: Angular target emits sibling `.rozie.ts` files next to
# each `.rozie` source so analogjs's TS Program (built from
# `tsconfig.app.json`'s `include` patterns) picks them up. These are
# generated build artefacts — never commit. Repo-wide so consumers using
# the Angular target via @rozie/unplugin in any subproject opt out
# automatically.
*.rozie.ts

# Phase 06.2 follow-up — cross-rozie composition shims. When a `.rozie`
# component declares a `<components>` block, the prebuild also writes a
# tiny re-export shim `<Name>.ts` next to `<Name>.rozie.ts` so TS module
# resolution can find `import './<Name>'` (the extensionless cross-rozie
# convention). The shim files start with the marker `// @rozie-cross-rozie-shim`
# and are detected/skipped if a consumer-authored same-named file exists.
# Listed per consumer demo here because we can't gitignore the bare `.ts`
# pattern repo-wide without sweeping legitimate consumer code.
examples/consumers/angular-analogjs/src/Counter.ts
examples/consumers/angular-analogjs/src/CardHeader.ts
examples/consumers/lit-vanilla-demo/src/rozie/Counter.ts
examples/consumers/lit-vanilla-demo/src/rozie/CardHeader.ts
examples/consumers/react-vite/src/Counter.ts
examples/consumers/react-vite/src/CardHeader.ts
examples/consumers/svelte-vite/src/Counter.ts
examples/consumers/svelte-vite/src/CardHeader.ts
# Phase 07.2 Plan 06 — ModalConsumer dogfood composes Modal + WrapperModal
# via <components>; the prebuild emits Modal.ts + WrapperModal.ts shims
# alongside their .rozie sources. Same gitignore pattern.
examples/consumers/angular-analogjs/src/Modal.ts
examples/consumers/angular-analogjs/src/WrapperModal.ts
examples/consumers/lit-vanilla-demo/src/rozie/Modal.ts
examples/consumers/lit-vanilla-demo/src/rozie/WrapperModal.ts
examples/consumers/react-vite/src/Modal.ts
examples/consumers/react-vite/src/WrapperModal.ts
examples/consumers/svelte-vite/src/Modal.ts
examples/consumers/svelte-vite/src/WrapperModal.ts
# Quick task 260515-1y4: when the visual-regression rig builds the angular
# target, `prebuildExtraRoots: [<repo>/examples]` extends the disk-cache
# walker to the top-level `examples/` directory, which causes shims for any
# composition target to be emitted at the repo's `examples/` root. Glob
# (non-recursive — no trailing `**`) is safe here: there are no legitimate
# authored `.ts` files at `examples/` root, only `.rozie` source and
# subdirectories.
examples/*.ts

# Phase 20 — @rozie-ui/sortable-list moved SortableList.rozie into the package
# source dir. When any consumer/docs/VR build compiles the Angular target with
# `prebuildExtraRoots` reaching this package, the prebuild emits a transient
# `// @rozie-cross-rozie-shim` re-export `SortableList.ts` next to the .rozie
# source (KanbanColumn composes SortableList via <components>). It is a
# regenerated build artefact — never commit. Same per-location convention as
# the consumer-demo shims above (bare `.ts` can't be ignored package-wide
# without sweeping the codegen-emitted leaf sources).
packages/ui/sortable-list/src/SortableList.ts

# @rozie-ui/flatpickr — same Phase-20 packaging move as sortable-list above:
# Flatpickr.rozie lives in the package source dir, and the Angular prebuild
# (reaching this package via `prebuildExtraRoots`) emits a transient
# `// @rozie-cross-rozie-shim` re-export `Flatpickr.ts` next to the .rozie
# source when a consumer composes it via <components> (FlatpickrDemo). It is a
# regenerated build artefact — never commit. (The sibling `Flatpickr.rozie.ts`
# disk-cache is already covered by the global `*.rozie.ts` rule above.)
packages/ui/flatpickr/src/Flatpickr.ts

# Phase 37 — @rozie-ui/maplibre + @rozie-ui/rete gained MULTIPLE compound-
# component .rozie sources in their package src dirs (MapLibre + Source + Layer;
# FlowCanvas + FlowNode + Handle + Connection). When a consumer composes them via
# <components> (the declarative demos), the Angular prebuild emits a transient
# `// @rozie-cross-rozie-shim` re-export `<Name>.ts` next to EACH .rozie source.
# These are regenerated build artefacts — never commit. The ONLY legitimate
# tracked files in these two src dirs are `.rozie` sources (the leaf `.ts` outputs
# live under packages/<target>/src/), so a dir-wide `*.ts` glob safely ignores
# only the shims and auto-covers future sibling children (vs. a per-file entry).
packages/ui/maplibre/src/*.ts
packages/ui/rete/src/*.ts

# Phase 48 — @rozie-ui/data-table (DataTable + Column compound family): same
# cross-rozie-shim story as maplibre/rete above. The Angular prebuild emits a
# transient `// @rozie-cross-rozie-shim` `Column.ts` (and any future child) next
# to the .rozie source, and the VR `build-cells.mjs` sweep deletes it — so a
# committed copy just churns. Only `.rozie` sources are legit-tracked here (leaf
# `.ts` outputs live under packages/<target>/src/); dir-wide `*.ts` ignores only
# the regenerated shims.
packages/ui/data-table/src/*.ts

